aka cara tries to make her livejournal not look like the crappiest piece of crappy crap ever.

I had a very high-profile party tonight.  VIPs only.  It was so select and so elite, only i was good enough to come to the party.  So i had a mood-lighting scantly-clad sexy-rave by myself.

Actually. It was pretty fun.  I thought about taking pictures, but considering what i was wearing, i thought it might be able to be construed as child pornography.  Many of my male friends who were online at the time were deeply disappointed.

Evidently, my online presence radiantes sexiness.  All the people who know me in real live laugh at this comment.  Because i am a an ugly little kid who trips over herself all the time.

On another note, last night was way much fun.  Even though i was still the first person to fall asleep, because i can't stay awake when other people around for some odd strange reason.  I bet i end up falling asleep during sex.  You know, once i can actually start having sex in beds, instead of all the other creepy odd places teenagers are forced to have sex in.

Wait, scratch all that.  Once i start having sex period.

But the limo ride and dinner at hard rock cafe with everyone was way cool.  including the coaster beanie hats that laure and catherine got for celebrating their first "eighteenth birthday".  I'm disappointed i didn't get to see all of Nightmare Before Christmas though, since i've never seen it straight through.  *sigh*

AND there was no Chundo time.  Which was sad as well.  Honestly, what kind of party is it if we all don't stay up until three and then watch William Wegman videos?!   With a couple of drinks, those videos would be even more hillarious than they already are.

Okay, enough strange comments about my life.  Back to reading Hot Gimmick and staying up late again.  I'll have time to sleep once i'm forced into bed at nine every night "to set a good example" for the little kids at my grandmothers.  Oh god, i don't think i'll make it!  Where is Christopher when i need him?!

Blah life, man.

You know, while we're still semi on the topic of strange bands that nobody really listens to ever, i'd just like to say that i love Chumbawamba.  Yes, those one-hit-wonder kids that brought the world "tubthumper", a song that i didn't realize at the time was completely about getting shit-faced.

Well, they weren't one-hit-wonders to Cara.  I fucking love the song "On Ebay".  Perhaps because i am a super nerd.  But it entertains me.  And it's a lot better than "tubthumper" ever was.  Go watch the video on launch.  You might be impressed.

In order to keep up the spirit of thanksgiving, i am thankful for the following things:

me, myself, and i.

But also: mo rocca, "come on eileen", solitude, makeup remover, sims 2, my fifteen minutes of fame, the postal service, macbeth finger puppets, extra long fake pearl necklaces, fresh cranberries, yahoo radio, fleece blankets, the lack of police officers on my route to school, sanity, rationality, kitty clocks, j-drama, black gel ink pens, perfect timing, night, sari skirts, almond joys, daisies, "the stars of track and field", cirque de soliel, and pie.

Pecan pie.  And if you pronounce it "pea-can", i punch you in the face, fucktard.

What i am not thankful for: my dog miles.  my parents were highly angered because i excluded him when i said i was thankful for my family.  Don't push it people, i could have told the truth and said i was thankful for my family's money, and then what would your reaction have been?

Oh, and alarm systems.  Not to fond of those either.

Dear Universe,

Why is it on a night like tonight, where all i have to do is read four pages for english and do five problems for math, do you have to throw in something like a test?

I mean, really, i was looking forward to a night of coming home, doing my homework, and then, say, sleeping from five o'clock on.  However, not the case.

Did i not make my point about my absolute exhaustedness when i slept through the majority of journalism today?  Was it not totally obvious that i needed to sleep?

But oh no.  On the one night this week, and even this weekend, that i will be able to sleep... you spite me with a test.

DAMN YOU.

Sincerly,

Miss Cara M. McConnell

Karma.




                       i will get you some day!









In other news, who's for running into lost lovers at the most unopportune times?  'Cause i am!

*bites lower lip* i'm going to get in trouble.  Bad thoughts lead to bad moves lead to bad situations.

And bad situations mean more meetings with the therapist.  Ugh.

Just one comment, really: WHY DO THERE HAVE TO BE SO MANY RULES?  WHY CAN'T I JUST DO WHAT I WANT AND FEEL WHAT I WANT TO FEEL?

That's all, mostly.

I've been thinking about radically changing my appearance.  I've always wanted to dye my hair, tint it red or make it a little darker, or navy blue.  I've always thought that dying my hair navy blue would be really fun.  Or grey.  Grey would be pretty interesting, especially since it is a "natural color" and therefore fair game for during the school year. Ursuline would hate me, which would thoroughly please me.

Another thing i have been thinking about is piercing something.  I don't really want to pierce my ears, i mean, if it hurt when i got the first ear pierced i'd flip out and wouldn't get the second one pierce and it would be bad news, really. That, and ear piercings... i dunno, everyone does it.  I just have never really been into it.  I'm sorta thinking about piercing my nose.  I mean, why not.  My mother would totally flip out though.  I'd have to do it myself.

If i put Oragel on my nose, do you think it would hurt less?

Ah... i dunno.  Creepster.

Today, is a day of mourning.

Today, Stuart Wilson was evicted from the U.K. Big Brother house.

While i was in England i became addicted to the original, better, and much more raunchier version of Big Brother.  I imediately started pulling for Stuart, who was much more laid back and much better looking than the other housemates.  And now he's gone.

He was the fifth to last person pulled from the house.  No one had voted for him to be put up for eviction the entire time he was in the house.  Not even the public voted him out.  No, the great Big Brother gods just decided to pluck Stuart from the house randomly.

I think they were intimidated by Stuarts utter coolness.  I threw a fit when i read the news.  Borderline crying.  He was beautiful, guys.

Goodbye Stuart.

-end shallow fangirl posting-

Thanks for all the reassurence and respect guys.
